Step 1: Create a namespace of h92 

Step 2: Create a pod and define the volume/volume mount :

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx
  namespace: h92
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:1.21.6
    volumeMounts:
    - name: nginx-run
      mountPath: /var/run
    - name: nginx-cache
      mountPath: /var/cache/nginx
    - name: nginx-data
      mountPath: /usr/local/nginx
  volumes:
  - name: nginx-run
    emptyDir: {}
  - name: nginx-cache
    emptyDir: {}
  - name: nginx-data
    emptyDir: {}
	
Verification :	

C:\Users\thani\Kubernetes>kubectl get pods -n h92
NAME    READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE
nginx   1/1     Running   0          2m13s

By using describe command we can see the volumes :

Volumes:
  nginx-run:
    Type:       EmptyDir (a temporary directory that shares a pod's lifetime)
    Medium:
    SizeLimit:  <unset>
  nginx-cache:
    Type:       EmptyDir (a temporary directory that shares a pod's lifetime)
    Medium:
    SizeLimit:  <unset>
  nginx-data:
    Type:       EmptyDir (a temporary directory that shares a pod's lifetime)
    Medium:
    SizeLimit:  <unset>

Step 3: 

To ensure the nginx can only write to those Volume mount paths but not the container's temporary file we have to set the below condition in the yaml

Use readOnlyRootFilesystem: true in the containerâ€™s securityContext.
securityContext:
      readOnlyRootFilesystem: true


